      • normalize

        public static String normalize(String molStruct)
                        throws MolFormatException
        Converts the String representation of this molecule into a "normalized" String representation to implement some chemical equivalencies.
        1. Aromatize.
        2. Ungroup shortcut groups.
        3. Remove spin state information from radicals.
        4. Converts every single bond of the form (S|Se|N|P|As)m+–(O|S|Se|N|C)n– into (S|Se|N|P|As)(m – 1)+=(O|S|Se|N|C)(n – 1)–, and treat similar double bonds similarly.
        5. For every stereo bond, if it is from a nonstereocenter to a stereocenter or to a double-bond atom, flip it. This will make sure that the student's response with opposite convention will be treated as correct.
        Parameters:
        molStruct - String representation of a molecule
        Returns:
        String representation of the normalized molecule
        Throws:
        MolFormatException - if the molecule can't be imported

      • normalize

        public static Molecule normalize(Molecule origMol)
        Converts a copy of this molecule into a "normalized" form to implement some chemical equivalencies.
        1. Aromatize.
        2. Ungroup shortcut groups.
        3. Remove spin state information from radicals.
        4. Converts every single bond of the form (S|Se|N|P|As)m+–(O|S|Se|N|C)n– into (S|Se|N|P|As)(m – 1)+=(O|S|Se|N|C)(n – 1)–, and treat similar double bonds similarly.
        5. For every stereo bond, if it is from a nonstereocenter to a stereocenter or to a double-bond atom, flip it. This will make sure that the student's response with opposite convention will be treated as correct.
        Parameters:
        origMol - a molecule
        Returns:
        normalized copy of the original molecule

      • mechNormalize

        public static Molecule mechNormalize(Molecule origMol)
        Converts a copy of this molecule into a "normalized" form to implement some chemical equivalencies.
        1. Aromatize.
        2. Remove spin state information from radicals.
        3. For every stereo bond, if it is from a nonstereocenter to a stereocenter or to a double-bond atom, flip it. This will make sure that the student's response with opposite convention will be treated as correct.
        4. Remove unbonded multicenter attachment points.
        Parameters:
        origMol - a molecule
        Returns:
        normalized copy of the original molecule

        5. For every stereo bond, if it is from a nonstereocenter to a stereocenter or to a double-bond atom, flip it. This will make sure that the student's response with opposite convention will be treated as correct.

      • normalizeNoClone

        public static void normalizeNoClone(Molecule mol,
                                    boolean isMech)
        Converts this molecule into a "normalized" form to implement some chemical equivalencies. Modifies the original molecule!
        1. Aromatize.
        2. Remove spin state information from radicals.
        3. For every stereo bond, if it is from a nonstereocenter to a stereocenter or to a double-bond atom, flip it. This will make sure that the student's response with opposite convention will be treated as correct.
        4. Ungroup shortcut groups (nonmechanisms only).
        5. Converts every single bond of the form (S|Se|N|P|As)m+–(O|S|Se|N|C)n– into (S|Se|N|P|As)(m – 1)+=(O|S|Se|N|C)(n – 1)–, and treat similar double bonds similarly (nonmechanisms only).
        Parameters:
        mol - a molecule
        isMech - whether this molecule represents a mechanism

      • normalizeRadicals

        public static void normalizeRadicals(Molecule mol)
        Removes spin state information from radicals to allow the match/search to work. Atoms with RAD2_SINGLET and RAD2_TRIPLET are set to RAD2, and atoms with RAD3_DOUBLET and RAD3_QUARTET are set to RAD3.
        Parameters:
        mol - a molecule

      • normalizeRadical

        public static void normalizeRadical(MolAtom atom)
        Removes spin state information from radicals to allow the match/search to work. Atoms with DIVALENT_SINGLET and DIVALENT_TRIPLET are set to DIVALENT, and atoms with TRIVALENT_DOUBLET and TRIVALENT_QUARTET are set to MONOVALENT.
        Parameters:
        atom - an atom

      • normalizeStereoBonds

      • normalizeCoordinateBonds

        public static Molecule normalizeCoordinateBonds(Molecule mol)
        Makes a copy, and converts every coordinate bond X→Y in the copy not involving a multiatom group to X(+)-Y(-), and removes multicenter attachment points that aren't attached to anything. Always called before a MolCompare method is run, which is why it doesn't need to be done as part of standard normalization.
        Parameters:
        mol - a molecule
        Returns:
        a copy of the molecule in which coordinate bonds are changed to regular single bonds

        Parameters:
        mol - a molecule
